        section.section-introduction
            .container
                .introduction-content
                    h1.content--title Introduction
                    p.content--intro As a brand marketer or agency executive, your team spends a big part of the day keeping busy with your brand’s or clients’ social channels; from Facebook and Twitter to Instagram and Pinterest. Just as a channel seemingly exists for every conceivable type of content and campaign, the range of social media management platforms to optimize your efforts and workflow is as widely varied. 
                    
                    .content--more
                        p When social media became a bedrock medium for brands to instantly engage with consumers, professionals like you in charge of strategic oversight and allocating resources realized quickly that certain aspects of social marketing reach peak efficiency when automated. Can you imagine manually tracking brand mentions or keeping an eye on your competitors across every social channel?
                        <br>

                        p The <strong>traditional</strong> social workflow consists of two platform types: those for listening and those for publishing. Here, a brand would create content, publish it, listen to users and then create more content. A new type of social intelligence platform has emerged — one that creates the <strong>modern</strong> social workflow and enables you to ideate, analyze and compare the channels, content, and campaigns of thousands of brands (including your own). While the traditional platforms are important and likely more well known, it’s the latter that pulls everything together and helps answer the critical questions…

                        p.steps <strong>What should we do? And does what we’re doing actually work?</strong>
                        <br>

                        p As the sheer number of available platforms can befuddle even seasoned social marketers, (have you seen a <a href="#"><span class="highlight">Lumascape</span></a> recently?) we put this guide together to provide you a quick but thorough overview of the modern social workflow, how these platforms fit, what their differences are, and how they can work together.

